                            <comment id="14963800" author="pauloricardomg" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2015 18:39:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Basically when reverting G1 settings on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10403&quot; title=&quot;Consider reverting to CMS GC on 3.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10403&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10403&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I accidentaly nuked the check from &lt;tt&gt;cassandra-env.ps1&lt;/tt&gt; that skips heap size calculation if the MAX_HEAP_SIZE variable is defined, so the ccm-defined MAX_HEAP_SIZE was being ignored. &lt;tt&gt;cassandra-env.sh&lt;/tt&gt; was not affected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached trivial patch that adds the check back. Tested locally and &lt;tt&gt;bootstrap_test.py:TestBootstrap.decommissioned_wiped_node_can_join_test&lt;/tt&gt; passes after the fix (before it was timing out).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests:&lt;/p&gt;
